<p>
<seg id=1> Albright, US state secretary, held a joint press reception on the 29th with Tang Jiaxuan, Foreign Minister of China, who is now visiting the US, and gave talks on Sino-American issues. </seg>
<seg id=2> Tang Jiaxuan also mentioned that the Lewinsky affair of president Clinton was one of America's internal matters, and that China would never forget president Clinton's contribution to the promotion of Sino-American friendship. </seg>
<seg id=3> Zhou Youkang, correspondent of VOA, reports from the press reception. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Here in the White House at 11:00 a.m. on the 29th US president Clinton met with the foreign minister of China, Tang Jiaxuan, who is here on a visit to in Washington. </seg>
<seg id=5> US State Secretary Albright announced the news at the joint press reception held with Tang Jiaxuan at the state council at noon on the 29th. </seg>
<seg id=6> Albright said, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Albright said, I'm glad to tell you that foreign minister Tang Jiaxuan and president Clinton have just met and announced China's decision to sign the Convention on Civil Rights and Political Power in New York on October 5th. </seg>
<seg id=8> At the reception, Tang Jiaxuan, foreign minister of China, also said that the meeting with Clinton was very significant. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> President Clinton gave me a reception and I think our meeting was productive. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> At present, the president has some trouble and many people, domestic and abroad, are expressing their extreme dissatisfaction and criticisms of president Clinton because of his affair. </seg>
<seg id=11> Some suggested impeachment, some asked him to leave office by himself, some democratic congressmen even set a separated themselves from him. </seg>
<seg id=12> But foreign minister Tang Jiaxuan didn't avoid the issue, on the contrary, he highly praised president Clinton for his contribution to the promotion of Sino-American friendship. </seg>
<seg id=13> At the reception a reporter asked Tang Jiaxuan whether Clinton's affair would affect the Sino-American relationship. </seg>
<seg id=14> Tang Jiaxuan said, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=15> I think it's just an internal affair of the US. </seg>
<seg id=16> I never thought it would cause any trouble in the development of China's relationship to the states. </seg>
<seg id=17> President Clinton himself has contributed much to the development of Sino-American relations, which we will never forget. </seg>
<seg id=18> As for me, minister of foreign affairs of China, I sincerely hope the Sino-American relationship can substantially and steadily continue on the basis of the Three Joint Communique as well as the two leaders' joint declaration. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=19> CCP authorities have always been insisting that Taiwan is one of the provinces of China, and the Taiwan issue is an internal affair of China. </seg>
<seg id=20> Foreign Minister of China Tang Jiaxuan mentioned the Taiwan issues again and again when attending the UN general meetings and in public when visiting Washington. </seg>
<seg id=21> Only at the reception a reporter asked Tang Jiaxuan what was the biggest obstacle in the Sino-American strategic partnership, Tang Jiaxuan' answered, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=22> As we have talked about this several times, in this aspect the very attention should be paid to deal with the Taiwan issues. </seg>
<seg id=23> Because the Taiwan issue is the most sensitive as well as the most real issue in the Sino-American relation. </seg>
</p>
